<div class="home-content">
  <div>
    <h2>This is a blog built with Postwave.</h2>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/dorkrawk/postwave" title="Postwave">Postwave</a> is an opinionated flat-file based based blog engine.
    </p>
    <p>
      Posts are written as Markdown files and then displayed dynamically in a simple <a href="https://sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a> site using the built in <a href="https://github.com/dorkrawk/postwave?tab=readme-ov-file#displaying-posts" title="Postwave Ruby client">Postwave Ruby Client</a>. Check out the <a href="https://github.com/dorkrawk/postwave-site" title="code for this site on GitHub">code</a> for this site to see how to use Postwave in a real world situation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Learn more about <a href="../posts/what-is-postwave-for" title="What Is Postwave For?">what Postwave is</a> and <a href="../posts/how-to-set-up-postwave" title="How To Set Up Postwave">get started</a> using Postwave!
    </p>
  </div>
  <div id="post-index">
    <h3 class="right">Recent Posts</h3>
    <ul>
      <% @post_index.each do |post| %>
        <li>
          <div class="post-title">
            <a href="/posts/<%= post.slug %>"><%= post.title %></a> 
          </div>
          <div class="post-date">
            <%= post.date.strftime("%B %e, %Y") %>
          </div>
        </li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
    <div class="see-all-posts">
      <a href="/blog">View All Posts â†’</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div id="tags">
    <h3 class="right">Tags</h3>
    <ul>
      <% @tags.each do |tag| %>
        <li><a href="/tags/<%= tag %>"><%= tag %></a></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
